Subject: Re: [T2] Pushrod Seals

> It's time to change the leaking pushrod tube seals on my '76 Westy, it has the
> stock 2.0L with fuel injection. Since I'm going to be in there should I
> replace the pushrod tubes as well? Anything else that I should replace while
> I'm doing this?

Unless your tubes are damaged, no reason to replace them. Since you
have to pull the rockers and such off to do that, it's a good time to
check your valves to see if they're all at the same height. Variations
can mean valve seat problems.



